text: Main Hall/La Crosse State Normal School was the original building for La Crosse Normal School now the University of Wisconsin–La Crosse in La Crosse, Wisconsin. The building was constructed in 1909. The office of the chancellor and various administrative departments are in Main Hall.About Graff Main Hall. University of Wisconsin-La Crosse. The building is now known as the Maurice O. Graff Main Hall.La Crosse Tribune - 7.0 : Graff known as scholar with sense of humor The building as it appears currently ==References== Category:University and college buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:Buildings and structures in La Crosse, Wisconsin Category:University of Wisconsin–La Crosse Category:University and college administration buildings in the United States Category:National Register of Historic Places in La Crosse County, Wisconsin
